Title: Short & Special Episode: Education Revolution for Chronic Illness
Description: Struggling with chronic illness and want to pursue higher education? This week's bite-sized episode tackles the challenges of online learning for those with chronic conditions. We explore the limitations of traditional online programs and discuss a potential solution: Hybrid model: Core courses delivered through MOOC platforms (Coursera, edX) Local cohorts: Build community and collaboration through in-person meetups at co-working spaces. This is just the beginning! We want to hear your thoughts. What can we do to make education more accessible for people with chronic illness? Title: S2. : Are these simple things ruining your life?
Description: We are often so focused on developing new habits when it comes to achieving progress in life, whatever our goals may be, that we often forget about eliminating the bad habits. Doing this can actually be just as beneficial and quite often, bad habits are the real things that are holding us back to becoming better people. Here I discuss 7 of the most common bad habits I believe to be holding us back and how we can remove them from our lives.

Title: Multifamily Real Estate as an Investable Asset Class with Maxwell Wu
Description: EP 91: Multifamily Real Estate as an Investable Asset Class with Maxwell Wu The Real Estate Mastermind Live is a live podcast turned radio show, created for real estate investors who want to learn directly from top experts in all different asset classes. The Real Estate Mastermind Live is hosted by Seth Gershberg and Jay Tenenbaum of Scottsdale Mortgage Investments, and Edward Brown of Pacific Private Money. Today’s guest Maxwell Wu of Fulcrum lending and your hosts dive into the realm of multifamily real estate as an investable asset class in this episode of Real Estate Mastermind Live. Join our hosts Seth Gershberg, Jay Tenenbaum, and Edward Brown as they delve into insightful discussions with Maxwell, the founder of Fulcrum Lending, a direct balance sheet lender for multifamily properties nationwide. With Maxwell's extensive background in real estate investment and operations across Wall Street firms, this episode promises to unveil valuable insights into the multifamily real estate market. In this episode we dive into some of the following key topics: Private Credit in a Lending Slowdown: Discover how private credit has stepped up during the lending slowdown across the banking industry. PropTech in CRE Lending: Explore what makes PropTech attractive for commercial real estate (CRE) lending. Investing in Mortgage Debt: Learn how accredited investors and asset managers can invest in mortgage debt. Multifamily Credit Ratings: Understand how multifamily credit ratings differ from other asset classes such as industrial and retail. Post Certificate of Occupancy Lending: Explore why Fulcrum Lending focuses on post Certificate of Occupancy lending instead of construction. Front Running Freddie Mac and Fannie Mae: Gain insights into how to front run Freddie Mac and Fannie Mae lending opportunities. Exciting Catalysts for CRE: Hear Maxwell's perspective on the most exciting catalysts for CRE in the near future. Understanding Debt Types: Differentiate between preferred equity, bridge, mezzanine, and permanent debt in real estate investments. Join us as we explore the multifaceted world of multifamily real estate investing with Maxwell, and uncover the strategies and opportunities available in this dynamic asset class. Unlock the potential of multifamily real estate investing and gain invaluable insights into navigating this lucrative market on Real Estate Mastermind Live.
